But they have a choice _ the Europeans and Germans and Americans. Those misgivings are misplaced. Even if the history did not exist, there would be fears of that kind, he said. The East German state is collapsing, said Geyer. It could also mean, he said, that American troops might have to stay in Europe as a counterweight to Germany. West Germans were aware of their European neighbors' misgivings, said Richard Breitman of American University, and so they presented reunification within the context of European integration. We're dealing not just with rational calculation but a whole host of emotional memories. 